{
  "name": "agent-index-core",
  "display_name": "Agent-Index Core",
  "version": "3.5.0",
  "description": "Core infrastructure for the agent-index system. v3.5.0: publish-updates 3.2.0 — `--check-upstream` flag fetches latest infrastructure from GitHub before sync (closes the manual git-pull step); smart prerequisite detection auto-runs bootstrap-zip regen when triggered by file changes (closes bug 20260504-8d20ea22-6); shared `regenerate-bootstrap` subroutine extracted to templates/, called by both edit-org and publish-updates. Admin's release flow becomes one verb: `@ai:publish-updates --check-upstream`. v3.4.0: native Go permission-helper binary v0.2.0 + binary-distribution registry. v3.3.1: invite-member rewritten to delegate ACL grants to the permission-change-helper. v3.3.0: permission-change-helper skill + Node binary. v3.2.0: org-setup management dashboard fixes. v3.1.x: extended adapter contract v2.0. v3.0.x: natural language triggers, on-demand executor.",
  "author": "agent-index",
  "license": "proprietary",
  "category": "infrastructure",
  "agent_index_min_version": "3.0.0",
  "api": [
    "session-start",
    "member-bootstrap",
    {
      "name": "org-setup",
